  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\n## Problem\r\n\r\nWhen 1-1 command confirms or declines status then command indication about Incoming or Outgoing transaction changed to the it's opposite state\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n\r\nTransaction command keep the same state after Accept/Decline\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n\r\n![1113](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/8749671/81310830-49226200-908d-11ea-81c1-ac11ff20646a.gif)\r\n\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n1) UserA (with ETH) adds new UserB and they join 1-1 chat\r\n2) UserA sends a `Send` command (`Outgoing transaction` on UserA side)\r\n3) UserB receives it as `Incoming transaction`\r\n4) UserB taps -> any of `Access and share address` OR `Decline`\r\n**Actual result:** On UserA side and UserB side the command message changed status to the opposite one (so UserA who supposed to send transaction gets `Incoming transaction` with the `Sign and send` button and UserB sees on his side `Outgoing transaction`). And how it looks on UserB side you may see in above actual result gif\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status version: develop 8th of May\r\n- Operating System: Android and iOS",
